b'Qualifications'
b' Ph.D. Electrical Engineering Telecom-ParisTech (former Ecole Nationale Sup\xc3\xa9rieure des T\xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9communications de Paris), Paris, France, 2002'
b' M.S. (Laurea, summa cum laude) Electrical Engineering, specialization Communications Politecnico di Torino, Torino, Italy, 1998'
b'Research Interests'
b' Information theoretic limits of wireless interference networks, with special emphasis on cognitive radio and user cooperation.'
b' Design of closed-loop deep brain electrical stimulation for Parkinson\xe2\x80\x99s disease and essential tremor patients; joint work with the Neurosurgery Department at UIC.'
b' Cross-layer design of Hybrid ARQ protocols and resource allocation.'
b' Distortion exponent of multiple description coding and successive refinement for streaming multimedia content on multi-routes networks.'
b' Error analysis in loopy belief propagation.'
b'Professional Achievements'
b' Best Paper Award EW2002 (European Wireless)'
b' NSF Career Award 0643954'
b' Co-chair Communication Theory Symposium, the 2010 IEEE International Conference on Communications (ICC 2010)'
b' UIC COE Faculty Research Award 2010-2011'
b' Editor of IEEE Communications Letters 2006-2009'
b' Editor of IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications 2010-2014'
b' Associate Editor of IEEE Transactions on Information Theory 2014-present'
b' Senior Member IEEE'
b'Courses Offered'
